      RDFParser.DatatypeHandling ParserConfig.datatypeHandling()
      Deprecated. 
      Datatype handling is now split across BasicParserSettings.VERIFY_DATATYPE_VALUES, BasicParserSettings.FAIL_ON_UNKNOWN_DATATYPES and BasicParserSettings.NORMALIZE_DATATYPE_VALUES.

      This method will be removed in a future release.

      Methods in org.eclipse.rdf4j.rio with parameters of type RDFParser.DatatypeHandling 
      Modifier and Type Method and Description
      void RDFParser.setDatatypeHandling(RDFParser.DatatypeHandling datatypeHandling)
      Deprecated. 
      since 2.0. Use RDFParser.getParserConfig() with BasicParserSettings.FAIL_ON_UNKNOWN_DATATYPES, BasicParserSettings.VERIFY_DATATYPE_VALUES, and/or BasicParserSettings.NORMALIZE_DATATYPE_VALUES instead.
      Constructors in org.eclipse.rdf4j.rio with parameters of type RDFParser.DatatypeHandling 
      Constructor and Description
      ParserConfig(boolean verifyData, boolean stopAtFirstError, boolean preserveBNodeIDs, RDFParser.DatatypeHandling datatypeHandling)
      Deprecated. 
      Use ParserConfig.ParserConfig() instead and set preserveBNodeIDs using ParserConfig.set(RioSetting, Object) with BasicParserSettings.PRESERVE_BNODE_IDS.

      The other parameters are all deprecated and this constructor may be removed in a future release.

      This constructor calls #setNonFatalErrors using a best-effort algorithm that may not match the exact semantics of the pre-2.7 constructor.
